1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,200
Catalysts speed up reactions without being used up.

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:05,200
How do they do it?

3
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:08,000
In both industry and biology, they’re essential.

4
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,600
Think of them as secret agents in chemical reactions.

5
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:14,400
Without catalysts, many reactions would take ages.

6
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:18,400
They lower the energy needed to start, speeding up processes.

7
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:22,000
For example, enzymes are biological catalysts vital for digestion.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:24,800
Without them, we couldn’t break down food.

9
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,000
Catalysts are everywhere!

10
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:31,200
They’re not just in labs; they shape our world by making reactions efficient.

11
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:33,600
Curious to learn more about chemistry?

12
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:36,800
Hit that follow button for more fascinating science!
